<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9805> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9805" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/25> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 257-63" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9118> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9118" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 749, footnote 331" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7504> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7504" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He very probably had been praetor by 59, since his service as Caesar's legatus pro praetore was continuous from 58 to 50 (MRR), and in that year Caesar stationed him in Cisalpine Gaul quo maiore commendatione conciliaretur ad consulatus petitionem (Hirtius in BG 8.52.2).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5919> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5919" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He met his death as one of the Pompeian leaders at Munda in Spain, but no title is preserved (Bell. Hisp. 18.9; 31.9; Yell. 2.55.,1; Flor. 2.13.83; App. BC 2.105; Dio 43.38.2; Oros. 6.16.6-9)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5840> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5840" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably ranked as a Legate in the Pompeian forces, where dignitas counted for much, but in virtue of his military experience one of the most prominent of the commanders in the field in Africa (Bell. Afr., passim; Val. Max. 8.14.5; App. BC 2.95; Dio 43.2). After the defeat at Thapsus, he escaped to Spain (Dio 43.30.4; Oros. 6.16.6; cf. App. BC 2.87)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5766> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5766" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In Africa with the Pompeian forces, probably as a Legate (see 45, Legates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5701> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5701" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legate of Pompey (Caes. BC 3.13.3-4), and with him until Pharsalus (BC 3.19.6-7, and 71.4, and 87.1-7; Plut. Pomp. 68.1; Cic. 38.6; App. BC 2.62, at Dyrrachium). He fled to Corcyra, then accompanied Cato (see above, Promagistrates) with the intention of joining Pompey, and later reached Africa (Cic. Div. 1.68; Auct. Bell. Afr. 19.3-4; Frontin. Str. 2.7.13; Plut. Cat. Min. 57.2; Dio 42.10.3; cf. App. BC 2.87, to Spain; Lucan 9.550 and 566)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5588> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5588" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus pro praetore under Caesar (see 50, Legates). He joined Pompey in January, 49 (Cic.Att.7.11.1, and 12.5, and 13.1, and 13A.3, and 15.3, and 16.1-2; 8.2.3; Fam. 14.14.2; 16.12.4; cf. Hirt. in Caes. BG 8.52.3, and Caes. BC 1.15.2; Plut. Caes. 34.2-3; Pomp. 64.3; Dio 41.4.2-4; cf. Lucan 5.345-347, and Schol. Bern. on Lucan, p. 167 Usener), and became an important Legate under him (see Caes. BC 3.13.3-4; and 48, Legates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5476> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5476" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus pro praetore under Caesar in Gaul, who received charge of Cisalpine Gaul in 50 (Hirt. in Caes. BG 8.52.2-3; on his wealth, see Cic. Att. 7.7.6; Caes. BC 1.15.2; Val. Max. 8.14.5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5413> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5413" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus pro praetore under Caesar in Gaul (Hirt. in Caes. BG 8.6.3, 23-25, and 45; Dio 40.43.1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5360> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5360" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus pro praetore under Caesar in Gaul. In this year he performed particularly important service against the tribes of the Seine valley (Caes. BG 7.34.2, and 56-62, and 86-87,and 90.4; Dio 40.38.4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5296> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5296" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus pro praetore under Caesar in Gaul; active this year in reducing the Treviri and the Menapii to submission (Caes. Ba 6.5.6, and 33; Dio, 40.31; Oros. 6.10.16)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5258> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5258" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus pro praetore under Caesar in Gaul. Held command in Gaul during Caesar's expedition to Britain, and held the territory of the Treviri during the uprising (Caes. BG 5.8.1, and 11.3-4, and 23.4, and 24.2, and 37.7, and 46.4, and 47.4-5, and 53, and 55-58; Cic. QF 3.8.2; Dio 40.11; Oros. 6.10.10-12)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5208> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5208" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus pro praetore under Caesar in Gaul (see 58, Legates; Caes. BG 4.38.1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5160> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5160" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus pro praetore under Caesar, and in charge of the region along the Rhine (Caes. BG 3.11. 1). See Schol. Bern. on Lucan 5.345, p. 167 U." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5102> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5102" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus pro praetore under Caesar in Gaul (Caes. BG 2.1.1, 11.3, and 26.4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5064> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5064" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Caesar as Legatus pro praetore (Caes. BG 1.21, cf. 10, and 54; Plut. Caes. 18.2; 34.2; Pomp. 64.3; App. Celt. 15; Schol. Bern., on Lucan 5.345, p. 167 U)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4859> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4859" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "1 The election of the Pontifex Maximus was probably not affected by these laws (L. B,. Taylor, CPh 37 [1942] 421 ff.; see Pontifices), but remained according to the ancient procedure." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4858> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4858" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Carried a bill instituting the trial of Rabirius for treason (Cic. Rab. Perd., passim; Quintil. Inst. Or. 5.13.20; Dio 37.26.1-28.4, and 37.2; cf. Cic. Pis. 4; Att. 2.1.3); and a law to restore the election of priests to the people as under the Lex Domitia of 104 (Dio 37.37.1-2). See above, on Ampius Balbus." .
